      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription on this stone is complete, though the stone itself is in two pieces. A tabula ansata in relief frames the standard Greek funerary text. Both names mentioned are Jewish. This stone may have been placed in a mausoleum; it is elaborate and smoothly dressed, and does not have the tall, shaft-like shape of an ordinary tombstone.</p>
         </div>
